FT  19 MAR 94 / First steps to peace
Bill Clinton with Bosnian president Alija Izetbegovic and Croatian president
Franjo Tudjman after the signing in Washington of an agreement binding
Bosnian Croats and Moslems in a loose federation. Mr Clinton said the deal
offered 'one of the first clear signals that parties to this conflict are
willing to end the violence'.
